## Add color: `aes(color = ...)`

Map a variable to the **color** aesthetic to distinguish groups:

. . .

:::{.columns}

:::{.column width="50%"}


::: {.cell flourish='[{"target":"color = continent"}]'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  gapminder,
  aes(
    x = gdpPercap,
    y = lifeExp,
    color = continent
  )
) +
  geom_point()
```
:::


- `color = continent` maps the continent to point color
- A legend is added automatically

